# .env.example — example environment variables for the contact form
# Copy to a local file (e.g. .env.local) or set these in your hosting provider dashboard.

# -----------------------
# SMTP (Gmail example)
# If you use Gmail, generate an App Password (recommended) and use it as SMTP_PASS.
# Do NOT commit real secrets. Use .env.local (local) or platform env vars (Vercel/Netlify).
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
# The SMTP user (Gmail address that will send the emails)
SMTP_USER=avannaemmanuel@gmail.com
# App Password generated in Google (see instructions below)
SMTP_PASS=

# The "from" address used in outgoing emails (preferably the same as SMTP_USER)
CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL=avannaemmanuel@gmail.com
# The contact address that will RECEIVE contact form emails
CONTACT_TO_EMAIL=avannabenito2@gmail.com

# -----------------------
# WhatsApp (optional)
# If set, the server will include a pre-filled wa.me link in the email for quick messaging
# Use international format (leading +).
WHATSAPP_NUMBER=+22968731360

# -----------------------
# Front-end override (optional)
# When the front-end should call a different URL for the contact API (production), set this.
# Example: REACT_APP_CONTACT_ENDPOINT=https://yourdomain.com/api/contact
REACT_APP_CONTACT_ENDPOINT=

# -----------------------
# Usage notes & Gmail instructions (summary):
# 1) Use a dedicated mailbox for contact (recommended): e.g. contact@yourdomain.tld or your@gmail.com
# 2) For Gmail personal accounts: enable 2FA on the Google account, then create an App Password
#    (Google Account → Security → App passwords → Select "Mail" / "Other" → generate). Copy
#    the generated 16-character password and set it as SMTP_PASS.
# 3) For Google Workspace (G Suite): if App Passwords are disabled, ask your admin to allow
#    SMTP relay or create a dedicated service account / SMTP credentials with the provider.
# 4) CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL should generally match SMTP_USER to avoid being blocked by the mail provider.
# 5) Do NOT commit secrets. Keep this file as `.env.example` only; place real values in `.env.local`
#    (for local dev) or in your hosting provider's environment variables panel.

# -----------------------
# Quick local-test checklist (PowerShell):
# cd D:\\Bric-group-App_web
